(17, 1, '<h3><strong>Family Background</strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Shea Bell has had a deep passion for sports, especially baseball, since the day he could grip the wiffle ball bat. Shea is one of 4 sons of DJ and Laura Bell. DJ Bell grew up in Crawford, NE where he pitched in High School and at Chadron State University while getting his degree. Laura Bell was born and raised in Fort Collins, CO where she attended Poudre High School, and played all sports along with cheerleading before going to Chadron State University to get her degree. The Bell family has been born and bread to have a passion for sports.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>With 4 boys that passion started with the first born Brycen. Brycen Bell played at Rocky Mountain earning numerous honors both academically and athletically. From Rocky, Brycen continued his career at Garden City Community College and Texas A&amp;M Corpus Christi University. He then played 4 seasons of Pro ball in the Pecos League, including two seasons overseas in Australia.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The two middle children are Shea and Trevor Bell. Trevor Bell also played at Rocky Mountain High School and Garden City Community college before he continued his career at Truman State University. While at Truman, he went to a D-2 College world Series with the Bulldogs. Trevor is now finishing up his degree in Physics at Truman State.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The youngest brother is Chad Bell. Chad Bell, like all the other Bell boys, played at Rocky Mountain. Chad earned a State Championship with the Lobos along with some athletic and academic honors. From there, Chad went to Western Nevada Community College where he played 1 season and then got recruited to play at Louisiana-Monroe University in the Sunbelt Conference. Chad is currently a junior at Monroe and is hoping to continue his strong baseball career with another promising season.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Shea loves all sports, hiking/outdoors, and spending time with his family and friends when he isn&rsquo;t at the facility.</p>\r\n', 'a:2:{i:0;s:40:\"uploads/instructor/1644277316_shea-1.jpg\";i:1;s:40:\"uploads/instructor/1644277316_shea-2.jpg\";}', 1, 0, '2022-02-07 18:41:56', '2022-02-07 18:41:56', NULL),
(18, 1, '<h3><strong>Baseball Background</strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>2 Year Letter with Rocky Mountain High School with 2 of those years being State Champions</li>\r\n	<li>2 Year Starter at Garden City Community College\r\n	<ul>\r\n		<li>1 Sub regional Title</li>\r\n		<li>Conference Champions</li>\r\n		<li>All Conference Honors</li>\r\n	</ul>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>2 Year Starter at Coker College\r\n	<ul>\r\n		<li>2 Time Gold Glove Nominee</li>\r\n		<li>1 Conference Championship and Ring</li>\r\n		<li>1 Regional Title and Ring</li>\r\n		<li>1 College World Series Appearance</li>\r\n		<li>Interest from several MLB teams</li>\r\n	</ul>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>2 Years of Professional Baseball\r\n	<ul>\r\n		<li>Captain of the Garden City Wind and Starting Short Stop</li>\r\n		<li>Conference Championship with the Trinidad Triggers</li>\r\n	</ul>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n', 'a:1:{i:0;s:40:\"uploads/instructor/1644277339_shea-3.jpg\";}', 1, 0, '2022-02-07 18:42:19', '2022-02-07 18:42:19', NULL),
(19, 1, '<h3><strong>Coaching Background</strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>1 Year Assistant JV Coach at Rocky Mountain High School​</li>\r\n	<li>1 Year Varsity Hitting and Fielding Coach at Poudre High School</li>\r\n	<li>3 Years of Private lessons spanning from Hitting, Pitching, Fielding Lessons all the way to Speed and Agility/Power sessions.</li>\r\n	<li>2 Year as the Owner/Head Coach of the Colorado BB&rsquo;s High School Showcase Team\r\n	<ul>\r\n		<li>4 Seniors signed in their first year​</li>\r\n	</ul>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n', NULL, 1, 0, '2022-02-07 18:42:49', '2022-02-07 18:42:49', NULL),
